### Configure Per-Agent Sandbox and Tool Restrictions

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/concepts/multi-agent.md

This JSON configuration defines sandbox and tool restrictions for individual agents. It allows specifying workspace paths, sandbox modes (off, all), Docker setup commands, and explicit lists of allowed or denied tools for each agent. This enables granular control over agent environments and capabilities.

```json
{
  "agents": {
    "list": [
      {
        "id": "personal",
        "workspace": "~/.openclaw/workspace-personal",
        "sandbox": {
          "mode": "off"  // No sandbox for personal agent
        }
        // No tool restrictions - all tools available
      },
      {
        "id": "family",
        "workspace": "~/.openclaw/workspace-family",
        "sandbox": {
          "mode": "all",     // Always sandboxed
          "scope": "agent",  // One container per agent
          "docker": {
            // Optional one-time setup after container creation
            "setupCommand": "apt-get update && apt-get install -y git curl"
          }
        },
        "tools": {
          "allow": ["read"],                    // Only read tool
          "deny": ["exec", "write", "edit", "apply_patch"]    // Deny others
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

