### Pin Job to Specific Agent (Bash)

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md

This bash command shows how to add a cron job and explicitly pin it to a specific agent named 'ops'. If the 'ops' agent is unavailable, the job will fall back to the default agent configuration. This is useful for multi-agent setups.

```bash
openclaw cron add --name "Ops sweep" --cron "0 6 * * *" --session isolated --message "Check ops queue" --agent ops
```

