### Setup Anthropic Authentication on Gateway Host

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/help/faq.md

Provides commands to set up Anthropic authentication directly on the gateway host, either by generating a setup token or pasting one obtained from another machine. This is crucial for configuring the gateway to communicate with Anthropic services.

```bash
openclaw models auth setup-token --provider anthropic
```

```bash
openclaw models auth paste-token --provider anthropic
```

