### Configure Work Agent with Shared Sandbox

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/multi-agent-sandbox-tools.md

This JSON configuration sets up two agents, 'personal' without sandbox restrictions and 'work' with a shared Docker sandbox. The 'work' agent is granted specific tools for reading, writing, applying patches, and executing commands, while restricting browser and gateway access.

```json
{
  "agents": {
    "list": [
      {
        "id": "personal",
        "workspace": "~/.openclaw/workspace-personal",
        "sandbox": { "mode": "off" }
      },
      {
        "id": "work",
        "workspace": "~/.openclaw/workspace-work",
        "sandbox": {
          "mode": "all",
          "scope": "shared",
          "workspaceRoot": "/tmp/work-sandboxes"
        },
        "tools": {
          "allow": ["read", "write", "apply_patch", "exec"],
          "deny": ["browser", "gateway", "discord"]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

