### Configure Different Sandbox Modes per Agent

Source: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/blob/main/docs/multi-agent-sandbox-tools.md

This JSON configuration establishes a global default sandbox mode ('non-main', session scope) and then overrides it for specific agents. The 'main' agent is explicitly set to 'off' for sandboxing, while the 'public' agent is configured for 'all' agent-scoped sandboxing with restricted tools.

```json
{
  "agents": {
    "defaults": {
      "sandbox": {
        "mode": "non-main",  // Global default
        "scope": "session"
      }
    },
    "list": [
      {
        "id": "main",
        "workspace": "~/.openclaw/workspace",
        "sandbox": {
          "mode": "off"  // Override: main never sandboxed
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "public",
        "workspace": "~/.openclaw/workspace-public",
        "sandbox": {
          "mode": "all",  // Override: public always sandboxed
          "scope": "agent"
        },
        "tools": {
          "allow": ["read"],
          "deny": ["exec", "write", "edit", "apply_patch"]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

